			<tr>
				<td valign="top">Comment:</td>
				<td>Atta dialect. Mambila is spoken on and near the Mambila plateau straddling the Nigeria-Cameroon border. Perrin & Hill (1969) analyze the tone system as consisting of four level tones which can combine to form two rising, two falling, and one rise-fall contour on monosyllables. A form of vowel harmony restricts sequences of vowels in disyllables. Any vowel except /a/ can follow itself; only /e/ follows /a/. Also /a/ can follow /i,e,u/, /e/ can follow /i,u/ and /i/ can follow /u/. Vowels are nasalized after /h/.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td valign="top">Source(s):</td>
